5189 /*
5190  * The returned cgroup is fully initialized including its control mask, but
5191  * it isn't associated with its kernfs_node and doesn't have the control
5192  * mask applied.
5193  */
5194 static struct cgroup *cgroup_create(struct cgroup *parent, const char *name,
     /*   */
5195                                     umode_t mode)
5196 {
5197         struct cgroup_root *root = parent->root;
5198         struct cgroup *cgrp, *tcgrp;
5199         struct kernfs_node *kn;
5200         int level = parent->level + 1;
5201         int ret;
5202 
5203         /* allocate the cgroup and its ID, 0 is reserved for the root */
5204         cgrp = kzalloc(struct_size(cgrp, ancestor_ids, (level + 1)),
5205                        GFP_KERNEL);
5206         if (!cgrp)
5207                 return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
5208 
5209         ret = percpu_ref_init(&cgrp->self.refcnt, css_release, 0, GFP_KERNEL);
5210         if (ret)
5211                 goto out_free_cgrp;
5212 
5213         if (cgroup_on_dfl(parent)) {
5214                 ret = cgroup_rstat_init(cgrp);
5215                 if (ret)
5216                         goto out_cancel_ref;
5217         }
5218 
5219         /* create the directory */
5220         kn = kernfs_create_dir(parent->kn, name, mode, cgrp);
5221         if (IS_ERR(kn)) {
5222                 ret = PTR_ERR(kn);
5223                 goto out_stat_exit;
5224         }
5225         cgrp->kn = kn;
5226 
5227         init_cgroup_housekeeping(cgrp);
5228 
5229         cgrp->self.parent = &parent->self;
5230         cgrp->root = root;
5231         cgrp->level = level;
5232 
5233         ret = psi_cgroup_alloc(cgrp);
5234         if (ret)
5235                 goto out_kernfs_remove;
5236 
5237         ret = cgroup_bpf_inherit(cgrp);
5238         if (ret)
5239                 goto out_psi_free;
5240 
5241         /*
5242          * New cgroup inherits effective freeze counter, and
5243          * if the parent has to be frozen, the child has too.
5244          */
5245         cgrp->freezer.e_freeze = parent->freezer.e_freeze;
5246         if (cgrp->freezer.e_freeze) {
5247                 /*
5248                  * Set the CGRP_FREEZE flag, so when a process will be
5249                  * attached to the child cgroup, it will become frozen.
5250                  * At this point the new cgroup is unpopulated, so we can
5251                  * consider it frozen immediately.
5252                  */
5253                 set_bit(CGRP_FREEZE, &cgrp->flags);
5254                 set_bit(CGRP_FROZEN, &cgrp->flags);
5255         }
5256 
5257         spin_lock_irq(&css_set_lock);
5258         for (tcgrp = cgrp; tcgrp; tcgrp = cgroup_parent(tcgrp)) {
5259                 cgrp->ancestor_ids[tcgrp->level] = cgroup_id(tcgrp);
5260 
5261                 if (tcgrp != cgrp) {
5262                         tcgrp->nr_descendants++;
5263 
5264                         /*
5265                          * If the new cgroup is frozen, all ancestor cgroups
5266                          * get a new frozen descendant, but their state can't
5267                          * change because of this.
5268                          */
5269                         if (cgrp->freezer.e_freeze)
5270                                 tcgrp->freezer.nr_frozen_descendants++;
5271                 }
5272         }
5273         spin_unlock_irq(&css_set_lock);
5274 
5275         if (notify_on_release(parent))
5276                 set_bit(CGRP_NOTIFY_ON_RELEASE, &cgrp->flags);
5277 
5278         if (test_bit(CGRP_CPUSET_CLONE_CHILDREN, &parent->flags))
5279                 set_bit(CGRP_CPUSET_CLONE_CHILDREN, &cgrp->flags);
5280 
5281         cgrp->self.serial_nr = css_serial_nr_next++;
5282 
5283         /* allocation complete, commit to creation */
5284         list_add_tail_rcu(&cgrp->self.sibling, &cgroup_parent(cgrp)->self.children);
5285         atomic_inc(&root->nr_cgrps);
5286         cgroup_get_live(parent);
5287 
5288         /*
5289          * On the default hierarchy, a child doesn't automatically inherit
5290          * subtree_control from the parent.  Each is configured manually.
5291          */
5292         if (!cgroup_on_dfl(cgrp))
5293                 cgrp->subtree_control = cgroup_control(cgrp);
5294 
5295         cgroup_propagate_control(cgrp);
5296 
5297         return cgrp;
5298 
5299 out_psi_free:
5300         psi_cgroup_free(cgrp);
5301 out_kernfs_remove:
5302         kernfs_remove(cgrp->kn);
5303 out_stat_exit:
5304         if (cgroup_on_dfl(parent))
5305                 cgroup_rstat_exit(cgrp);
5306 out_cancel_ref:
5307         percpu_ref_exit(&cgrp->self.refcnt);
5308 out_free_cgrp:
5309         kfree(cgrp);
5310         return ERR_PTR(ret);
5311 }
5312 
5313 static bool cgroup_check_hierarchy_limits(struct cgroup *parent)
     /*   */
5314 {
5315         struct cgroup *cgroup;
5316         int ret = false;
5317         int level = 1;
5318 
5319         lockdep_assert_held(&cgroup_mutex);
5320 
5321         for (cgroup = parent; cgroup; cgroup = cgroup_parent(cgroup)) {
5322                 if (cgroup->nr_descendants >= cgroup->max_descendants)
5323                         goto fail;
5324 
5325                 if (level > cgroup->max_depth)
5326                         goto fail;
5327 
5328                 level++;
5329         }
5330 
5331         ret = true;
5332 fail:
5333         return ret;
5334 }

5336 int cgroup_mkdir(struct kernfs_node *parent_kn, const char *name, umode_t mode)
     /*   */
5337 {
5338         struct cgroup *parent, *cgrp;
5339         int ret;
5340 
5341         /* do not accept '\n' to prevent making /proc/<pid>/cgroup unparsable */
5342         if (strchr(name, '\n'))
5343                 return -EINVAL;
5344 
5345         parent = cgroup_kn_lock_live(parent_kn, false);
5346         if (!parent)
5347                 return -ENODEV;
5348 
5349         if (!cgroup_check_hierarchy_limits(parent)) {
5350                 ret = -EAGAIN;
5351                 goto out_unlock;
5352         }
5353 
5354         cgrp = cgroup_create(parent, name, mode);
5355         if (IS_ERR(cgrp)) {
5356                 ret = PTR_ERR(cgrp);
5357                 goto out_unlock;
5358         }
5359 
5360         /*
5361          * This extra ref will be put in cgroup_free_fn() and guarantees
5362          * that @cgrp->kn is always accessible.
5363          */
5364         kernfs_get(cgrp->kn);
5365 
5366         ret = cgroup_kn_set_ugid(cgrp->kn);
5367         if (ret)
5368                 goto out_destroy;
5369 
5370         ret = css_populate_dir(&cgrp->self);
5371         if (ret)
5372                 goto out_destroy;
5373 
5374         ret = cgroup_apply_control_enable(cgrp);
5375         if (ret)
5376                 goto out_destroy;
5377 
5378         TRACE_CGROUP_PATH(mkdir, cgrp);
5379 
5380         /* let's create and online css's */
5381         kernfs_activate(cgrp->kn);
5382 
5383         ret = 0;
5384         goto out_unlock;
5385 
5386 out_destroy:
5387         cgroup_destroy_locked(cgrp);
5388 out_unlock:
5389         cgroup_kn_unlock(parent_kn);
5390         return ret;
5391 }

5393 /*
5394  * This is called when the refcnt of a css is confirmed to be killed.
5395  * css_tryget_online() is now guaranteed to fail.  Tell the subsystem to
5396  * initate destruction and put the css ref from kill_css().
5397  */
5398 static void css_killed_work_fn(struct work_struct *work)
     /*   */
5399 {
5400         struct cgroup_subsys_state *css =
5401                 container_of(work, struct cgroup_subsys_state, destroy_work);
5402 
5403         mutex_lock(&cgroup_mutex);
5404 
5405         do {
5406                 offline_css(css);
5407                 css_put(css);
5408                 /* @css can't go away while we're holding cgroup_mutex */
5409                 css = css->parent;
5410         } while (css && atomic_dec_and_test(&css->online_cnt));
5411 
5412         mutex_unlock(&cgroup_mutex);
5413 }
5414 
5415 /* css kill confirmation processing requires process context, bounce */
5416 static void css_killed_ref_fn(struct percpu_ref *ref)
     /*   */
5417 {
5418         struct cgroup_subsys_state *css =
5419                 container_of(ref, struct cgroup_subsys_state, refcnt);
5420 
5421         if (atomic_dec_and_test(&css->online_cnt)) {
5422                 INIT_WORK(&css->destroy_work, css_killed_work_fn);
5423                 queue_work(cgroup_destroy_wq, &css->destroy_work);
5424         }
5425 }
5426 
5427 /**
5428  * kill_css - destroy a css
5429  * @css: css to destroy
5430  *
5431  * This function initiates destruction of @css by removing cgroup interface
5432  * files and putting its base reference.  ->css_offline() will be invoked
5433  * asynchronously once css_tryget_online() is guaranteed to fail and when
5434  * the reference count reaches zero, @css will be released.
5435  */
5436 static void kill_css(struct cgroup_subsys_state *css)
     /*   */
5437 {
5438         lockdep_assert_held(&cgroup_mutex);
5439 
5440         if (css->flags & CSS_DYING)
5441                 return;
5442 
5443         css->flags |= CSS_DYING;
5444 
5445         /*
5446          * This must happen before css is disassociated with its cgroup.
5447          * See seq_css() for details.
5448          */
5449         css_clear_dir(css);
5450 
5451         /*
5452          * Killing would put the base ref, but we need to keep it alive
5453          * until after ->css_offline().
5454          */
5455         css_get(css);
5456 
5457         /*
5458          * cgroup core guarantees that, by the time ->css_offline() is
5459          * invoked, no new css reference will be given out via
5460          * css_tryget_online().  We can't simply call percpu_ref_kill() and
5461          * proceed to offlining css's because percpu_ref_kill() doesn't
5462          * guarantee that the ref is seen as killed on all CPUs on return.
5463          *
5464          * Use percpu_ref_kill_and_confirm() to get notifications as each
5465          * css is confirmed to be seen as killed on all CPUs.
5466          */
5467         percpu_ref_kill_and_confirm(&css->refcnt, css_killed_ref_fn);
5468 }
5469 
5470 /**
5471  * cgroup_destroy_locked - the first stage of cgroup destruction
5472  * @cgrp: cgroup to be destroyed
5473  *
5474  * css's make use of percpu refcnts whose killing latency shouldn't be
5475  * exposed to userland and are RCU protected.  Also, cgroup core needs to
5476  * guarantee that css_tryget_online() won't succeed by the time
5477  * ->css_offline() is invoked.  To satisfy all the requirements,
5478  * destruction is implemented in the following two steps.
5479  *
5480  * s1. Verify @cgrp can be destroyed and mark it dying.  Remove all
5481  *     userland visible parts and start killing the percpu refcnts of
5482  *     css's.  Set up so that the next stage will be kicked off once all
5483  *     the percpu refcnts are confirmed to be killed.
5484  *
5485  * s2. Invoke ->css_offline(), mark the cgroup dead and proceed with the
5486  *     rest of destruction.  Once all cgroup references are gone, the
5487  *     cgroup is RCU-freed.
5488  *
5489  * This function implements s1.  After this step, @cgrp is gone as far as
5490  * the userland is concerned and a new cgroup with the same name may be
5491  * created.  As cgroup doesn't care about the names internally, this
5492  * doesn't cause any problem.
5493  */
5494 static int cgroup_destroy_locked(struct cgroup *cgrp)
     /*   */
5495         __releases(&cgroup_mutex) __acquires(&cgroup_mutex)
5496 {
5497         struct cgroup *tcgrp, *parent = cgroup_parent(cgrp);
5498         struct cgroup_subsys_state *css;
5499         struct cgrp_cset_link *link;
5500         int ssid;
5501 
5502         lockdep_assert_held(&cgroup_mutex);
5503 
5504         /*
5505          * Only migration can raise populated from zero and we're already
5506          * holding cgroup_mutex.
5507          */
5508         if (cgroup_is_populated(cgrp))
5509                 return -EBUSY;
5510 
5511         /*
5512          * Make sure there's no live children.  We can't test emptiness of
5513          * ->self.children as dead children linger on it while being
5514          * drained; otherwise, "rmdir parent/child parent" may fail.
5515          */
5516         if (css_has_online_children(&cgrp->self))
5517                 return -EBUSY;
5518 
5519         /*
5520          * Mark @cgrp and the associated csets dead.  The former prevents
5521          * further task migration and child creation by disabling
5522          * cgroup_lock_live_group().  The latter makes the csets ignored by
5523          * the migration path.
5524          */
5525         cgrp->self.flags &= ~CSS_ONLINE;
5526 
5527         spin_lock_irq(&css_set_lock);
5528         list_for_each_entry(link, &cgrp->cset_links, cset_link)
5529                 link->cset->dead = true;
5530         spin_unlock_irq(&css_set_lock);
5531 
5532         /* initiate massacre of all css's */
5533         for_each_css(css, ssid, cgrp)
5534                 kill_css(css);
5535 
5536         /* clear and remove @cgrp dir, @cgrp has an extra ref on its kn */
5537         css_clear_dir(&cgrp->self);
5538         kernfs_remove(cgrp->kn);
5539 
5540         if (parent && cgroup_is_threaded(cgrp))
5541                 parent->nr_threaded_children--;
5542 
5543         spin_lock_irq(&css_set_lock);
5544         for (tcgrp = cgroup_parent(cgrp); tcgrp; tcgrp = cgroup_parent(tcgrp)) {
5545                 tcgrp->nr_descendants--;
5546                 tcgrp->nr_dying_descendants++;
5547                 /*
5548                  * If the dying cgroup is frozen, decrease frozen descendants
5549                  * counters of ancestor cgroups.
5550                  */
5551                 if (test_bit(CGRP_FROZEN, &cgrp->flags))
5552                         tcgrp->freezer.nr_frozen_descendants--;
5553         }
5554         spin_unlock_irq(&css_set_lock);
5555 
5556         cgroup1_check_for_release(parent);
5557 
5558         cgroup_bpf_offline(cgrp);
5559 
5560         /* put the base reference */
5561         percpu_ref_kill(&cgrp->self.refcnt);
5562 
5563         return 0;
5564 };
5565 
5566 int cgroup_rmdir(struct kernfs_node *kn)
     /*   */
5567 {
5568         struct cgroup *cgrp;
5569         int ret = 0;
5570 
5571         cgrp = cgroup_kn_lock_live(kn, false);
5572         if (!cgrp)
5573                 return 0;
5574 
5575         ret = cgroup_destroy_locked(cgrp);
5576         if (!ret)
5577                 TRACE_CGROUP_PATH(rmdir, cgrp);
5578 
5579         cgroup_kn_unlock(kn);
5580         return ret;
5581 }

5590 static void __init cgroup_init_subsys(struct cgroup_subsys *ss, bool early)
     /*   */
5591 {
5592         struct cgroup_subsys_state *css;
5593 
5594         pr_debug("Initializing cgroup subsys %s\n", ss->name);
5595 
5596         mutex_lock(&cgroup_mutex);
5597 
5598         idr_init(&ss->css_idr);
5599         INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ss->cfts);
5600 
5601         /* Create the root cgroup state for this subsystem */
5602         ss->root = &cgrp_dfl_root;
5603         css = ss->css_alloc(cgroup_css(&cgrp_dfl_root.cgrp, ss));
5604         /* We don't handle early failures gracefully */
5605         BUG_ON(IS_ERR(css));
5606         init_and_link_css(css, ss, &cgrp_dfl_root.cgrp);
5607 
5608         /*
5609          * Root csses are never destroyed and we can't initialize
5610          * percpu_ref during early init.  Disable refcnting.
5611          */
5612         css->flags |= CSS_NO_REF;
5613 
5614         if (early) {
5615                 /* allocation can't be done safely during early init */
5616                 css->id = 1;
5617         } else {
5618                 css->id = cgroup_idr_alloc(&ss->css_idr, css, 1, 2, GFP_KERNEL);
5619                 BUG_ON(css->id < 0);
5620         }
5621 
5622         /* Update the init_css_set to contain a subsys
5623          * pointer to this state - since the subsystem is
5624          * newly registered, all tasks and hence the
5625          * init_css_set is in the subsystem's root cgroup. */
5626         init_css_set.subsys[ss->id] = css;
5627 
5628         have_fork_callback |= (bool)ss->fork << ss->id;
5629         have_exit_callback |= (bool)ss->exit << ss->id;
5630         have_release_callback |= (bool)ss->release << ss->id;
5631         have_canfork_callback |= (bool)ss->can_fork << ss->id;
5632 
5633         /* At system boot, before all subsystems have been
5634          * registered, no tasks have been forked, so we don't
5635          * need to invoke fork callbacks here. */
5636         BUG_ON(!list_empty(&init_task.tasks));
5637 
5638         BUG_ON(online_css(css));
5639 
5640         mutex_unlock(&cgroup_mutex);
5641 }

5643 /**
5644  * cgroup_init_early - cgroup initialization at system boot
5645  *
5646  * Initialize cgroups at system boot, and initialize any
5647  * subsystems that request early init.
5648  */
5649 int __init cgroup_init_early(void)
     /*   */
5650 {
5651         static struct cgroup_fs_context __initdata ctx;
5652         struct cgroup_subsys *ss;
5653         int i;
5654 
5655         ctx.root = &cgrp_dfl_root;
5656         init_cgroup_root(&ctx);
5657         cgrp_dfl_root.cgrp.self.flags |= CSS_NO_REF;
5658 
5659         RCU_INIT_POINTER(init_task.cgroups, &init_css_set);
5660 
5661         for_each_subsys(ss, i) {
5662                 WARN(!ss->css_alloc || !ss->css_free || ss->name || ss->id,
5663                      "invalid cgroup_subsys %d:%s css_alloc=%p css_free=%p id:name=%d:%s\n",
5664                      i, cgroup_subsys_name[i], ss->css_alloc, ss->css_free,
5665                      ss->id, ss->name);
5666                 WARN(strlen(cgroup_subsys_name[i]) > MAX_CGROUP_TYPE_NAMELEN,
5667                      "cgroup_subsys_name %s too long\n", cgroup_subsys_name[i]);
5668 
5669                 ss->id = i;
5670                 ss->name = cgroup_subsys_name[i];
5671                 if (!ss->legacy_name)
5672                         ss->legacy_name = cgroup_subsys_name[i];
5673 
5674                 if (ss->early_init)
5675                         cgroup_init_subsys(ss, true);
5676         }
5677         return 0;
5678 }

5680 static u16 cgroup_disable_mask __initdata;
5681 
5682 /**
5683  * cgroup_init - cgroup initialization
5684  *
5685  * Register cgroup filesystem and /proc file, and initialize
5686  * any subsystems that didn't request early init.
5687  */
5688 int __init cgroup_init(void)
     /*   */
5689 {
5690         struct cgroup_subsys *ss;
5691         int ssid;
5692 
5693         BUILD_BUG_ON(CGROUP_SUBSYS_COUNT > 16);
5694         BUG_ON(cgroup_init_cftypes(NULL, cgroup_base_files));
5695         BUG_ON(cgroup_init_cftypes(NULL, cgroup1_base_files));
5696 
5697         cgroup_rstat_boot();
5698 
5699         /*
5700          * The latency of the synchronize_rcu() is too high for cgroups,
5701          * avoid it at the cost of forcing all readers into the slow path.
5702          */
5703         rcu_sync_enter_start(&cgroup_threadgroup_rwsem.rss);
5704 
5705         get_user_ns(init_cgroup_ns.user_ns);
5706 
5707         mutex_lock(&cgroup_mutex);
5708 
5709         /*
5710          * Add init_css_set to the hash table so that dfl_root can link to
5711          * it during init.
5712          */
5713         hash_add(css_set_table, &init_css_set.hlist,
5714                  css_set_hash(init_css_set.subsys));
5715 
5716         BUG_ON(cgroup_setup_root(&cgrp_dfl_root, 0));
5717 
5718         mutex_unlock(&cgroup_mutex);
5719 
5720         for_each_subsys(ss, ssid) {
5721                 if (ss->early_init) {
5722                         struct cgroup_subsys_state *css =
5723                                 init_css_set.subsys[ss->id];
5724 
5725                         css->id = cgroup_idr_alloc(&ss->css_idr, css, 1, 2,
5726                                                    GFP_KERNEL);
5727                         BUG_ON(css->id < 0);
5728                 } else {
5729                         cgroup_init_subsys(ss, false);
5730                 }
5731 
5732                 list_add_tail(&init_css_set.e_cset_node[ssid],
5733                               &cgrp_dfl_root.cgrp.e_csets[ssid]);
5734 
5735                 /*
5736                  * Setting dfl_root subsys_mask needs to consider the
5737                  * disabled flag and cftype registration needs kmalloc,
5738                  * both of which aren't available during early_init.
5739                  */
5740                 if (cgroup_disable_mask & (1 << ssid)) {
5741                         static_branch_disable(cgroup_subsys_enabled_key[ssid]);
5742                         printk(KERN_INFO "Disabling %s control group subsystem\n",
5743                                ss->name);
5744                         continue;
5745                 }
5746 
5747                 if (cgroup1_ssid_disabled(ssid))
5748                         printk(KERN_INFO "Disabling %s control group subsystem in v1 mounts\n",
5749                                ss->name);
5750 
5751                 cgrp_dfl_root.subsys_mask |= 1 << ss->id;
5752 
5753                 /* implicit controllers must be threaded too */
5754                 WARN_ON(ss->implicit_on_dfl && !ss->threaded);
5755 
5756                 if (ss->implicit_on_dfl)
5757                         cgrp_dfl_implicit_ss_mask |= 1 << ss->id;
5758                 else if (!ss->dfl_cftypes)
5759                         cgrp_dfl_inhibit_ss_mask |= 1 << ss->id;
5760 
5761                 if (ss->threaded)
5762                         cgrp_dfl_threaded_ss_mask |= 1 << ss->id;
5763 
5764                 if (ss->dfl_cftypes == ss->legacy_cftypes) {
5765                         WARN_ON(cgroup_add_cftypes(ss, ss->dfl_cftypes));
5766                 } else {
5767                         WARN_ON(cgroup_add_dfl_cftypes(ss, ss->dfl_cftypes));
5768                         WARN_ON(cgroup_add_legacy_cftypes(ss, ss->legacy_cftypes));
5769                 }
5770 
5771                 if (ss->bind)
5772                         ss->bind(init_css_set.subsys[ssid]);
5773 
5774                 mutex_lock(&cgroup_mutex);
5775                 css_populate_dir(init_css_set.subsys[ssid]);
5776                 mutex_unlock(&cgroup_mutex);
5777         }
5778 
5779         /* init_css_set.subsys[] has been updated, re-hash */
5780         hash_del(&init_css_set.hlist);
5781         hash_add(css_set_table, &init_css_set.hlist,
5782                  css_set_hash(init_css_set.subsys));
5783 
5784         WARN_ON(sysfs_create_mount_point(fs_kobj, "cgroup"));
5785         WARN_ON(register_filesystem(&cgroup_fs_type));
5786         WARN_ON(register_filesystem(&cgroup2_fs_type));
5787         WARN_ON(!proc_create_single("cgroups", 0, NULL, proc_cgroupstats_show));
5788 #ifdef CONFIG_CPUSETS
5789         WARN_ON(register_filesystem(&cpuset_fs_type));
5790 #endif
5791 
5792         return 0;
5793 }

5795 static int __init cgroup_wq_init(void)
     /*   */
5796 {
5797         /*
5798          * There isn't much point in executing destruction path in
5799          * parallel.  Good chunk is serialized with cgroup_mutex anyway.
5800          * Use 1 for @max_active.
5801          *
5802          * We would prefer to do this in cgroup_init() above, but that
5803          * is called before init_workqueues(): so leave this until after.
5804          */
5805         cgroup_destroy_wq = alloc_workqueue("cgroup_destroy", 0, 1);
5806         BUG_ON(!cgroup_destroy_wq);
5807         return 0;
5808 }

5822 /*
5823  * proc_cgroup_show()
5824  *  - Print task's cgroup paths into seq_file, one line for each hierarchy
5825  *  - Used for /proc/<pid>/cgroup.
5826  */
5827 int proc_cgroup_show(struct seq_file *m, struct pid_namespace *ns,
     /*   */
5828                      struct pid *pid, struct task_struct *tsk)
5829 {
5830         char *buf;
5831         int retval;
5832         struct cgroup_root *root;
5833 
5834         retval = -ENOMEM;
5835         buf = kmalloc(PATH_MAX, GFP_KERNEL);
5836         if (!buf)
5837                 goto out;
5838 
5839         mutex_lock(&cgroup_mutex);
5840         spin_lock_irq(&css_set_lock);
5841 
5842         for_each_root(root) {
5843                 struct cgroup_subsys *ss;
5844                 struct cgroup *cgrp;
5845                 int ssid, count = 0;
5846 
5847                 if (root == &cgrp_dfl_root && !cgrp_dfl_visible)
5848                         continue;
5849 
5850                 seq_printf(m, "%d:", root->hierarchy_id);
5851                 if (root != &cgrp_dfl_root)
5852                         for_each_subsys(ss, ssid)
5853                                 if (root->subsys_mask & (1 << ssid))
5854                                         seq_printf(m, "%s%s", count++ ? "," : "",
5855                                                    ss->legacy_name);
5856                 if (strlen(root->name))
5857                         seq_printf(m, "%sname=%s", count ? "," : "",
5858                                    root->name);
5859                 seq_putc(m, ':');
5860 
5861                 cgrp = task_cgroup_from_root(tsk, root);
5862 
5863                 /*
5864                  * On traditional hierarchies, all zombie tasks show up as
5865                  * belonging to the root cgroup.  On the default hierarchy,
5866                  * while a zombie doesn't show up in "cgroup.procs" and
5867                  * thus can't be migrated, its /proc/PID/cgroup keeps
5868                  * reporting the cgroup it belonged to before exiting.  If
5869                  * the cgroup is removed before the zombie is reaped,
5870                  * " (deleted)" is appended to the cgroup path.
5871                  */
5872                 if (cgroup_on_dfl(cgrp) || !(tsk->flags & PF_EXITING)) {
5873                         retval = cgroup_path_ns_locked(cgrp, buf, PATH_MAX,
5874                                                 current->nsproxy->cgroup_ns);
5875                         if (retval >= PATH_MAX)
5876                                 retval = -ENAMETOOLONG;
5877                         if (retval < 0)
5878                                 goto out_unlock;
5879 
5880                         seq_puts(m, buf);
5881                 } else {
5882                         seq_puts(m, "/");
5883                 }
5884 
5885                 if (cgroup_on_dfl(cgrp) && cgroup_is_dead(cgrp))
5886                         seq_puts(m, " (deleted)\n");
5887                 else
5888                         seq_putc(m, '\n');
5889         }
5890 
5891         retval = 0;
5892 out_unlock:
5893         spin_unlock_irq(&css_set_lock);
5894         mutex_unlock(&cgroup_mutex);
5895         kfree(buf);
5896 out:
5897         return retval;
5898 }

     /*   */

5931 /**
5932  * cgroup_css_set_fork - find or create a css_set for a child process
5933  * @kargs: the arguments passed to create the child process
5934  *
5935  * This functions finds or creates a new css_set which the child
5936  * process will be attached to in cgroup_post_fork(). By default,
5937  * the child process will be given the same css_set as its parent.
5938  *
5939  * If CLONE_INTO_CGROUP is specified this function will try to find an
5940  * existing css_set which includes the requested cgroup and if not create
5941  * a new css_set that the child will be attached to later. If this function
5942  * succeeds it will hold cgroup_threadgroup_rwsem on return. If
5943  * CLONE_INTO_CGROUP is requested this function will grab cgroup mutex
5944  * before grabbing cgroup_threadgroup_rwsem and will hold a reference
5945  * to the target cgroup.
5946  */
5947 static int cgroup_css_set_fork(struct kernel_clone_args *kargs)
     /*   */
5948         __acquires(&cgroup_mutex) __acquires(&cgroup_threadgroup_rwsem)
5949 {
5950         int ret;
5951         struct cgroup *dst_cgrp = NULL;
5952         struct css_set *cset;
5953         struct super_block *sb;
5954         struct file *f;
5955 
5956         if (kargs->flags & CLONE_INTO_CGROUP)
5957                 mutex_lock(&cgroup_mutex);
5958 
5959         cgroup_threadgroup_change_begin(current);
5960 
5961         spin_lock_irq(&css_set_lock);
5962         cset = task_css_set(current);
5963         get_css_set(cset);
5964         spin_unlock_irq(&css_set_lock);
5965 
5966         if (!(kargs->flags & CLONE_INTO_CGROUP)) {
5967                 kargs->cset = cset;
5968                 return 0;
5969         }
5970 
5971         f = fget_raw(kargs->cgroup);
5972         if (!f) {
5973                 ret = -EBADF;
5974                 goto err;
5975         }
5976         sb = f->f_path.dentry->d_sb;
5977 
5978         dst_cgrp = cgroup_get_from_file(f);
5979         if (IS_ERR(dst_cgrp)) {
5980                 ret = PTR_ERR(dst_cgrp);
5981                 dst_cgrp = NULL;
5982                 goto err;
5983         }
5984 
5985         if (cgroup_is_dead(dst_cgrp)) {
5986                 ret = -ENODEV;
5987                 goto err;
5988         }
5989 
5990         /*
5991          * Verify that we the target cgroup is writable for us. This is
5992          * usually done by the vfs layer but since we're not going through
5993          * the vfs layer here we need to do it "manually".
5994          */
5995         ret = cgroup_may_write(dst_cgrp, sb);
5996         if (ret)
5997                 goto err;
5998 
5999         ret = cgroup_attach_permissions(cset->dfl_cgrp, dst_cgrp, sb,
6000                                         !(kargs->flags & CLONE_THREAD));
6001         if (ret)
6002                 goto err;
6003 
6004         kargs->cset = find_css_set(cset, dst_cgrp);
6005         if (!kargs->cset) {
6006                 ret = -ENOMEM;
6007                 goto err;
6008         }
6009 
6010         put_css_set(cset);
6011         fput(f);
6012         kargs->cgrp = dst_cgrp;
6013         return ret;
6014 
6015 err:
6016         cgroup_threadgroup_change_end(current);
6017         mutex_unlock(&cgroup_mutex);
6018         if (f)
6019                 fput(f);
6020         if (dst_cgrp)
6021                 cgroup_put(dst_cgrp);
6022         put_css_set(cset);
6023         if (kargs->cset)
6024                 put_css_set(kargs->cset);
6025         return ret;
6026 }
6027 
6028 /**
6029  * cgroup_css_set_put_fork - drop references we took during fork
6030  * @kargs: the arguments passed to create the child process
6031  *
6032  * Drop references to the prepared css_set and target cgroup if
6033  * CLONE_INTO_CGROUP was requested.
6034  */
6035 static void cgroup_css_set_put_fork(struct kernel_clone_args *kargs)
     /*   */
6036         __releases(&cgroup_threadgroup_rwsem) __releases(&cgroup_mutex)
6037 {
6038         cgroup_threadgroup_change_end(current);
6039 
6040         if (kargs->flags & CLONE_INTO_CGROUP) {
6041                 struct cgroup *cgrp = kargs->cgrp;
6042                 struct css_set *cset = kargs->cset;
6043 
6044                 mutex_unlock(&cgroup_mutex);
6045 
6046                 if (cset) {
6047                         put_css_set(cset);
6048                         kargs->cset = NULL;
6049                 }
6050 
6051                 if (cgrp) {
6052                         cgroup_put(cgrp);
6053                         kargs->cgrp = NULL;
6054                 }
6055         }
6056 }

6058 /**
6059  * cgroup_can_fork - called on a new task before the process is exposed
6060  * @child: the child process
6061  *
6062  * This prepares a new css_set for the child process which the child will
6063  * be attached to in cgroup_post_fork().
6064  * This calls the subsystem can_fork() callbacks. If the cgroup_can_fork()
6065  * callback returns an error, the fork aborts with that error code. This
6066  * allows for a cgroup subsystem to conditionally allow or deny new forks.
6067  */
6068 int cgroup_can_fork(struct task_struct *child, struct kernel_clone_args *kargs)
     /*   */
6069 {
6070         struct cgroup_subsys *ss;
6071         int i, j, ret;
6072 
6073         ret = cgroup_css_set_fork(kargs);
6074         if (ret)
6075                 return ret;
6076 
6077         do_each_subsys_mask(ss, i, have_canfork_callback) {
6078                 ret = ss->can_fork(child, kargs->cset);
6079                 if (ret)
6080                         goto out_revert;
6081         } while_each_subsys_mask();
6082 
6083         return 0;
6084 
6085 out_revert:
6086         for_each_subsys(ss, j) {
6087                 if (j >= i)
6088                         break;
6089                 if (ss->cancel_fork)
6090                         ss->cancel_fork(child, kargs->cset);
6091         }
6092 
6093         cgroup_css_set_put_fork(kargs);
6094 
6095         return ret;
6096 }
6097 
6098 /**
6099  * cgroup_cancel_fork - called if a fork failed after cgroup_can_fork()
6100  * @child: the child process
6101  * @kargs: the arguments passed to create the child process
6102  *
6103  * This calls the cancel_fork() callbacks if a fork failed *after*
6104  * cgroup_can_fork() succeded and cleans up references we took to
6105  * prepare a new css_set for the child process in cgroup_can_fork().
6106  */
6107 void cgroup_cancel_fork(struct task_struct *child,
     /*   */
6108                         struct kernel_clone_args *kargs)
6109 {
6110         struct cgroup_subsys *ss;
6111         int i;
6112 
6113         for_each_subsys(ss, i)
6114                 if (ss->cancel_fork)
6115                         ss->cancel_fork(child, kargs->cset);
6116 
6117         cgroup_css_set_put_fork(kargs);
6118 }
6119 
6120 /**
6121  * cgroup_post_fork - finalize cgroup setup for the child process
6122  * @child: the child process
6123  *
6124  * Attach the child process to its css_set calling the subsystem fork()
6125  * callbacks.
6126  */
6127 void cgroup_post_fork(struct task_struct *child,
     /*   */
6128                       struct kernel_clone_args *kargs)
6129         __releases(&cgroup_threadgroup_rwsem) __releases(&cgroup_mutex)
6130 {
6131         struct cgroup_subsys *ss;
6132         struct css_set *cset;
6133         int i;
6134 
6135         cset = kargs->cset;
6136         kargs->cset = NULL;
6137 
6138         spin_lock_irq(&css_set_lock);
6139 
6140         /* init tasks are special, only link regular threads */
6141         if (likely(child->pid)) {
6142                 WARN_ON_ONCE(!list_empty(&child->cg_list));
6143                 cset->nr_tasks++;
6144                 css_set_move_task(child, NULL, cset, false);
6145         } else {
6146                 put_css_set(cset);
6147                 cset = NULL;
6148         }
6149 
6150         /*
6151          * If the cgroup has to be frozen, the new task has too.  Let's set
6152          * the JOBCTL_TRAP_FREEZE jobctl bit to get the task into the
6153          * frozen state.
6154          */
6155         if (unlikely(cgroup_task_freeze(child))) {
6156                 spin_lock(&child->sighand->siglock);
6157                 WARN_ON_ONCE(child->frozen);
6158                 child->jobctl |= JOBCTL_TRAP_FREEZE;
6159                 spin_unlock(&child->sighand->siglock);
6160 
6161                 /*
6162                  * Calling cgroup_update_frozen() isn't required here,
6163                  * because it will be called anyway a bit later from
6164                  * do_freezer_trap(). So we avoid cgroup's transient switch
6165                  * from the frozen state and back.
6166                  */
6167         }
6168 
6169         spin_unlock_irq(&css_set_lock);
6170 
6171         /*
6172          * Call ss->fork().  This must happen after @child is linked on
6173          * css_set; otherwise, @child might change state between ->fork()
6174          * and addition to css_set.
6175          */
6176         do_each_subsys_mask(ss, i, have_fork_callback) {
6177                 ss->fork(child);
6178         } while_each_subsys_mask();
6179 
6180         /* Make the new cset the root_cset of the new cgroup namespace. */
6181         if (kargs->flags & CLONE_NEWCGROUP) {
6182                 struct css_set *rcset = child->nsproxy->cgroup_ns->root_cset;
6183 
6184                 get_css_set(cset);
6185                 child->nsproxy->cgroup_ns->root_cset = cset;
6186                 put_css_set(rcset);
6187         }
6188 
6189         cgroup_css_set_put_fork(kargs);
6190 }

6192 /**
6193  * cgroup_exit - detach cgroup from exiting task
6194  * @tsk: pointer to task_struct of exiting process
6195  *
6196  * Description: Detach cgroup from @tsk.
6197  *
6198  */
6199 void cgroup_exit(struct task_struct *tsk)
     /*   */
6200 {
6201         struct cgroup_subsys *ss;
6202         struct css_set *cset;
6203         int i;
6204 
6205         spin_lock_irq(&css_set_lock);
6206 
6207         WARN_ON_ONCE(list_empty(&tsk->cg_list));
6208         cset = task_css_set(tsk);
6209         css_set_move_task(tsk, cset, NULL, false);
6210         list_add_tail(&tsk->cg_list, &cset->dying_tasks);
6211         cset->nr_tasks--;
6212 
6213         WARN_ON_ONCE(cgroup_task_frozen(tsk));
6214         if (unlikely(cgroup_task_freeze(tsk)))
6215                 cgroup_update_frozen(task_dfl_cgroup(tsk));
6216 
6217         spin_unlock_irq(&css_set_lock);
6218 
6219         /* see cgroup_post_fork() for details */
6220         do_each_subsys_mask(ss, i, have_exit_callback) {
6221                 ss->exit(tsk);
6222         } while_each_subsys_mask();
6223 }

6277 /**
6278  * css_tryget_online_from_dir - get corresponding css from a cgroup dentry
6279  * @dentry: directory dentry of interest
6280  * @ss: subsystem of interest
6281  *
6282  * If @dentry is a directory for a cgroup which has @ss enabled on it, try
6283  * to get the corresponding css and return it.  If such css doesn't exist
6284  * or can't be pinned, an ERR_PTR value is returned.
6285  */
6286 struct cgroup_subsys_state *css_tryget_online_from_dir(struct dentry *dentry,
     /*   */
6287                                                        struct cgroup_subsys *ss)
6288 {
6289         struct kernfs_node *kn = kernfs_node_from_dentry(dentry);
6290         struct file_system_type *s_type = dentry->d_sb->s_type;
6291         struct cgroup_subsys_state *css = NULL;
6292         struct cgroup *cgrp;
6293 
6294         /* is @dentry a cgroup dir? */
6295         if ((s_type != &cgroup_fs_type && s_type != &cgroup2_fs_type) ||
6296             !kn || kernfs_type(kn) != KERNFS_DIR)
6297                 return ERR_PTR(-EBADF);
6298 
6299         rcu_read_lock();
6300 
6301         /*
6302          * This path doesn't originate from kernfs and @kn could already
6303          * have been or be removed at any point.  @kn->priv is RCU
6304          * protected for this access.  See css_release_work_fn() for details.
6305          */
6306         cgrp = rcu_dereference(*(void __rcu __force **)&kn->priv);
6307         if (cgrp)
6308                 css = cgroup_css(cgrp, ss);
6309 
6310         if (!css || !css_tryget_online(css))
6311                 css = ERR_PTR(-ENOENT);
6312 
6313         rcu_read_unlock();
6314         return css;
6315 }

6331 /**
6332  * cgroup_get_from_path - lookup and get a cgroup from its default hierarchy path
6333  * @path: path on the default hierarchy
6334  *
6335  * Find the cgroup at @path on the default hierarchy, increment its
6336  * reference count and return it.  Returns pointer to the found cgroup on
6337  * success, ERR_PTR(-ENOENT) if @path doens't exist and ERR_PTR(-ENOTDIR)

     /*   */

6389 static u64 power_of_ten(int power)
     /*   */
6390 {
6391         u64 v = 1;
6392         while (power--)
6393                 v *= 10;
6394         return v;
6395 }
6396 
6397 /**
6398  * cgroup_parse_float - parse a floating number
6399  * @input: input string
6400  * @dec_shift: number of decimal digits to shift
6401  * @v: output
6402  *
6403  * Parse a decimal floating point number in @input and store the result in
6404  * @v with decimal point right shifted @dec_shift times.  For example, if
6405  * @input is "12.3456" and @dec_shift is 3, *@v will be set to 12345.
6406  * Returns 0 on success, -errno otherwise.
6407  *
6408  * There's nothing cgroup specific about this function except that it's
6409  * currently the only user.
6410  */
6411 int cgroup_parse_float(const char *input, unsigned dec_shift, s64 *v)
     /*   */
6412 {
6413         s64 whole, frac = 0;
6414         int fstart = 0, fend = 0, flen;
6415 
6416         if (!sscanf(input, "%lld.%n%lld%n", &whole, &fstart, &frac, &fend))
6417                 return -EINVAL;
6418         if (frac < 0)
6419                 return -EINVAL;
6420 
6421         flen = fend > fstart ? fend - fstart : 0;
6422         if (flen < dec_shift)
6423                 frac *= power_of_ten(dec_shift - flen);
6424         else
6425                 frac = DIV_ROUND_CLOSEST_ULL(frac, power_of_ten(flen - dec_shift));
6426 
6427         *v = whole * power_of_ten(dec_shift) + frac;
6428         return 0;
6429 }

6455 
6456 void cgroup_sk_alloc(struct sock_cgroup_data *skcd)
     /*   */
6457 {
6458         if (cgroup_sk_alloc_disabled) {
6459                 skcd->no_refcnt = 1;
6460                 return;
6461         }
6462 
6463         /* Don't associate the sock with unrelated interrupted task's cgroup. */
6464         if (in_interrupt())
6465                 return;
6466 
6467         rcu_read_lock();
6468 
6469         while (true) {
6470                 struct css_set *cset;
6471 
6472                 cset = task_css_set(current);
6473                 if (likely(cgroup_tryget(cset->dfl_cgrp))) {
6474                         skcd->val = (unsigned long)cset->dfl_cgrp;
6475                         cgroup_bpf_get(cset->dfl_cgrp);
6476                         break;
6477                 }
6478                 cpu_relax();
6479         }
6480 
6481         rcu_read_unlock();
6482 }
6483 
6484 void cgroup_sk_clone(struct sock_cgroup_data *skcd)
     /*   */
6485 {
6486         if (skcd->val) {
6487                 if (skcd->no_refcnt)
6488                         return;
6489                 /*
6490                  * We might be cloning a socket which is left in an empty
6491                  * cgroup and the cgroup might have already been rmdir'd.
6492                  * Don't use cgroup_get_live().
6493                  */
6494                 cgroup_get(sock_cgroup_ptr(skcd));
6495                 cgroup_bpf_get(sock_cgroup_ptr(skcd));
6496         }
6497 }
6498 
6499 void cgroup_sk_free(struct sock_cgroup_data *skcd)
     /*   */
6500 {
6501         struct cgroup *cgrp = sock_cgroup_ptr(skcd);
6502 
6503         if (skcd->no_refcnt)
6504                 return;
6505         cgroup_bpf_put(cgrp);
6506         cgroup_put(cgrp);
6507 }
6508 
6509 #endif  /* CONFIG_SOCK_CGROUP_DATA */

6550 static ssize_t show_delegatable_files(struct cftype *files, char *buf,
     /*   */
6551                                       ssize_t size, const char *prefix)
6552 {
6553         struct cftype *cft;
6554         ssize_t ret = 0;
6555 
6556         for (cft = files; cft && cft->name[0] != '\0'; cft++) {
6557                 if (!(cft->flags & CFTYPE_NS_DELEGATABLE))
6558                         continue;
6559 
6560                 if (prefix)
6561                         ret += snprintf(buf + ret, size - ret, "%s.", prefix);
6562 
6563                 ret += snprintf(buf + ret, size - ret, "%s\n", cft->name);
6564 
6565                 if (WARN_ON(ret >= size))
6566                         break;
6567         }
6568 
6569         return ret;
6570 }

6572 static ssize_t delegate_show(struct kobject *kobj, struct kobj_attribute *attr,
     /*   */
6573                               char *buf)
6574 {
6575         struct cgroup_subsys *ss;
6576         int ssid;
6577         ssize_t ret = 0;
6578 
6579         ret = show_delegatable_files(cgroup_base_files, buf, PAGE_SIZE - ret,
6580                                      NULL);
6581 
6582         for_each_subsys(ss, ssid)
6583                 ret += show_delegatable_files(ss->dfl_cftypes, buf + ret,
6584                                               PAGE_SIZE - ret,
6585                                               cgroup_subsys_name[ssid]);
6586 
6587         return ret;
6588 }
6589 static struct kobj_attribute cgroup_delegate_attr = __ATTR_RO(delegate);

     /*   */

6594         return snprintf(buf, PAGE_SIZE,
6595                         "nsdelegate\n"
6596                         "memory_localevents\n"
6597                         "memory_recursiveprot\n");
6598 }
